      <p><span style="font-size:16px;"><strong>NEW
      VOLUNTEERS&nbsp;</strong></span></p>

      <p><span style="font-size:14px;">Volunteering is easy as
      1-2-3!&nbsp;</span></p>

      <p><span style="font-size:14px;">1. Fill out the <a href=
      "/support/application">
      APPLICATION</a></span></p>

      <p><span style="font-size:14px;">2. Attend orientation</span></p>

      <p><span style="font-size:14px;">3. Come for your first shift or
      begin your project</span></p>

      <p style="text-align: justify;"><span style=
      "font-size:14px;"><strong>1) Fill out the <a href=
      "/support/application">
      APPLICATION</a></strong><br>
      <em>Please be sure to fill out the application <strong>in its
      entirety</strong>.&nbsp; As you fill it out, please think about how
      you could best help the Bike Depot serve our community and what you
      will get out of this service.&nbsp; In the future we will search
      your volunteer profile to approach you for special opportunities
      based on your interests.&nbsp; After we review and approve your
      application we will invite you to our next
      orientation.</em></span></p>

      <p style="text-align: justify;"><span style=
      "font-size:14px;"><strong>2) Attend an "informative
      interview"</strong><br>
      <em>These casual, informal meetings take about 20 minutes. We will
      discuss what you wrote in your volunteer application and get you
      plugged into a volunteer opportunity that suits your
      interests.</em></span></p>

      <p style="text-align: justify;"><span style=
      "font-size:14px;"><strong>3) Sign up for a shift and get
      started</strong><br>
      <em>On your first day we try to pair you with a more experienced
      volunteer, but depending on availability this might not
      happen.&nbsp; We have a several volunteer positions that you can
      jump right into and others that require more skill and
      training.</em></span></p>

      <p style="text-align: justify;"><br>
      <span style="font-size:14px;"><strong>Some positions and tasks we
      need help with</strong><br>
      • Bicycle wrenching - work on bikes<br>
      • Shop Leads – those with the skill to take charge of the shop for
      a weekly shift.<br>
      • Teach classes<br>
      • Greet and help customers and participants<br>
      • Sell bikes, parts and accessories<br>
      • Outreach and marketing<br>
      • Bike Collection Volunteer<br>
      • Manage events<br>
      • Fundraising and grant writing<br>
      • Website and marketing development<br>
      • An infinite number of other tasks both big and small!</span></p>

      <p style="text-align: justify;"><br>
      <span style="font-size:14px;"><strong>Benefits</strong><br>
      We offer generous benefits to dedicated volunteers that commit to a
      weekly/bi-weekly shift, a committee or a special project.&nbsp; Our
      benefit structure is as follows:<br>
      <br>
      Volunteer 12 hours/month = 15% off Bikes and Bike Gear<br>
      Volunteer 24 hours/month = 30% off Bikes and Bike Gear<br>
      Volunteer 24 hours/month + added responsibility* = cost of item +
      10% (employee discount)<br>
      *such as lead mechanic, committee chair, project manager,
      etc.</span></p>

      <p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size:14px;">Thank
      you so much for your interest in helping to further the mission of
      the Bike Depot.</span></p>
